            "answer_text": "Italy is a country of more than 80 million and Albania about 3 million. So is a bit unequal to speak for the bulk of the population. However, beginning with the tribes of Yapigis and Messapis, assumed to be Illyrian, there had been relation between both populations. In XV century, there was a wave of Albanians from both Albania and Greece that were located in the Kingdom of Naples and Sicily, that formed the nucleus of Albanian-Italians called Arberesh. in present day, about 500,000 Albanians moved to Italy after 1990. ",
